      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(scripts): warn when postinstall detects running gateway with stale module imports",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAfter `npm install -g openclaw` replaces dist files (upgrade, rollback, or reinstall), the running gateway process holds ESM module caches pointing to the old hash-named dist files. Inbound messages fail silently with `ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND` — the process appears healthy (systemd reports active/running, channels show connected) but messages are silently dropped.\n\nThis fix adds a best-effort TCP probe to `127.0.0.1:18789` during postinstall. When a gateway is detected, it prints a visible ASCII warning box suggesting `openclaw gateway restart`.\n\nUsers can suppress the warning with `OPENCLAW_DISABLE_POSTINSTALL_RESTART_WARNING=true`.\n\nFixes #92241\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Postinstall script now warns when a gateway is running with stale module imports.\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: WSL2 Ubuntu (Linux 6.6.87.2-microsoft-standard-WSL2), Node v22.22.2\n\n**Exact steps or command run after fix**:\n\n```bash\n$ pnpm test -- test/scripts/postinstall-bundled-plugins.test.ts\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n\n```\n. postinstall$ node scripts/postinstall-bundled-plugins.mjs\n. postinstall:   ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n. postinstall:   ║  WARNING: OpenClaw gateway restart recommended              ║\n. postinstall:   ║  ...\n. postinstall:   ║  Run:  openclaw gateway restart                              ║\n. postinstall:   ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n. postinstall: Done\n```\n\nThe warning appeared automatically — the postinstall detected the development gateway running on port 18789.\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: On each `npm install -g` (or `pnpm install` triggering postinstall), if the gateway is running on the default port, users will see a clear ASCII warning suggesting restart. The check is best-effort with 1s timeout — it silently skips if the gateway isn't running or is on a non-default port.\n\n**What was not tested**: Gateways on non-default ports, behind TLS proxies, or in containers. The TCP probe only checks 127.0.0.1:18789. A running gateway on a custom port would not trigger the warning.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n39/39 tests passed (all existing + no regression):\n\n```\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  39 passed (39)\n   Start at  14:21:38\n   Duration  1.91s\n```\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**Yes** — a console warning is printed when a running gateway is detected during postinstall. This is the intended improvement.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**No** — existing env flags (`OPENCLAW_DISABLE_BUNDLED_PLUGIN_POSTINSTALL`) continue to work. A new opt-out env var (`OPENCLAW_DISABLE_POSTINSTALL_RESTART_WARNING`) is additive only.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**Minimal** — a TCP connect to 127.0.0.1:18789 with 1s timeout. No data is sent or received. The socket is destroyed immediately on successful connect. Loopback-only, no external network access.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n- Unexpected false positive: a non-gateway process listening on 18789 could trigger the warning. False negatives (missed gateway on non-default port) are safe — no warning is better than a wrong warning.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n- The warning text is advisory only (\"restart recommended\"), not an error. A false positive causes no harm beyond a visual suggestion. The 1s timeout prevents the postinstall from hanging.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n- Maintainer review\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-92241-gateway-stale-module-imports",
